title: `cargo check`-invoked Rustc 10x slower since `nightly-2019-10-03`

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: I-hang
labels.description: Issue: The compiler never terminates, due to infinite loops, deadlock, livelock, etc.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
Starting `nightly-2019-10-03`, Rustc ~~**hangs forever**~~ is about 10x slower while building my project (Linux x86-64). It works fine on `nightly-2019-10-01` and earlier versions. In between, `nightly-2019-10-02` has an ICE.

I am only invoking `cargo check`.

See below for the ICE and the thread backtraces while rustc is hanging.
